$ sed example: colorizing a file

This examples replaces `RED`, `YLW` and `GRN` with the → Linux/shell/ANSI-escape-sequences for red, yellow and green. This can be used as a template to
colorize files (for example errors and warnings in a log file).

{ The script

  gh|about-sed|/ansi-escape||

}
{ The input file - colorize

  gh|about-sed|/testfiles/colorize||

}

